narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: You must be prepared to write a great number of personal responses and essays. Each of them though has its own interesting subject for opinion. Take this class.

Madness and Civilization was a great section of English 114. I would recommend it to any student. We read a lot of interesting material and the discussions really made you think. It definitely made me think about madness in a different light. Getting an A isn't easy but taking the class is definitely worth it because it will help you to learn how to write better and it will make you think.

I would recommend taking this class only if you are truly interested in the subject matter, otherwise I would recommend taking a more gently introductory course. Do not take this class just because it is a seminar, there are other lectures with more interesting material that I would have rather taken. Also because of the teacher's requirement that an A paper must be eligible to submit to the departmental english awards, the grading in this glass is very harsh.
This class is a good introductory English class. When choosing a section, make sure you are interested in the subject that is being discussed; doing so will make the class much more enjoyable.
